    "actions_taken": [
      "Field helicopter evacuation within 15 minutes",
      "Transport to West Jefferson Hospital in New Orleans",
      "Emergency room amputation of fingertip",
      "Placement on restricted work duty greater than 3 days",
      "Scheduled cosmetic hand surgery on 22 October 2020"
    ],
    "summary": "On 18 October 2020 at 0820 hours at MC 243 A (Matterhorn), a crane mechanic's finger was crushed while transporting a 55-gallon drum of hydraulic oil across the platform deck using a hand dolly. The drum and dolly were lifted onto a 12-inch high I-beam which personnel could not pull across. When an operator left to get assistance, the injured person attempted to secure the dolly on the beam. The dolly slipped from the injured person's grip and their right hand middle finger was caught between the dolly handle and the skid beam, crushing the fingertip. The injury required evacuation and amputation of the fingertip.",
    "recommendations": [],
